The paper deals with motion analysis and understanding using volumetric approaches, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of spectral methods such as locally linear embedding suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and data analysis (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the potential for tracking motion cues, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO).
